Anna Okon The Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency has pledged to facilitate fast release of 19 seafarers who were abducted on board a tanker vessel, Nave Constellation. The 19 seafarers, 18 of Indian origin and one of Turkish origin were abducted near Egina FPSO, 100 nautical miles off Bonny Island on Tuesday. Nine crew members were left onboard the vessel following the attack. The Director General, NIMASA, Dr Dakuku Peterside, stated that the agency was working with relevant partners to ensure theÂ  crew onboard the vessel were secured and safe. He spoke in Abuja on Thursday, on the sideline of the ongoing National Transportation Summit organised by the Chartered Institute of Transport Administration of Nigeria, according to a statement from NIMASA. Copyright PUNCH.
